title: Suburban shops must diversify to take on major centres in battle for consumers
text:
Suburban shops must diversify to take... Suburban shops must diversify to take on major centres in battle for consumers 44 min ago Read more: Sydney Morning Herald 
Business owners and managers at the Ainslie shops, from left, Niki Katsibiris, Irene Mihailakis, Manuel Xyrakis, Colette Needham, Bruno Paressant, and Keith Mihailakis. Canberra's suburban shops will fall prey to larger retail centres unless they reinvent themselves and diversify, a national property advisory group says.   Sydney Morning Herald.
